        "title": "Use Cronet for playback, simplify YouTube DataSource, and increase connection timeouts",
        "user": {
            "login": "AudricV",
            "id": 74829229,
            "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjc0ODI5MjI5",
            "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/74829229?v=4",
            "gravatar_id": "",
            "url": "https://api.github.com/users/AudricV",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/AudricV",
            "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/AudricV/followers",
            "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/AudricV/following{/other_user}",
            "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/AudricV/gists{/gist_id}",
            "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/AudricV/starred{/owner}{/repo}",
            "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/AudricV/subscriptions",
            "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/AudricV/orgs",
            "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/AudricV/repos",
            "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/AudricV/events{/privacy}",
            "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/AudricV/received_events",
            "type": "User",
            "site_admin": false
        },
        "body": "#### What is it?\r\n\r\n- [x] Feature (user facing)\r\n- [x] Codebase improvement (dev facing)\r\n\r\n#### Description of the changes in your PR\r\n\r\nThis PR adds support of QUIC and Brotli content-encoding for playback, by using the [Cronet network stack](https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src/+/refs/heads/main/components/cronet/README.md).\r\n\r\nIt replaces usage of Android's network stack for playback (with `HttpUrlConnection`), which is OS version and device specific, and so can be easily outdated and can contain some issues that are not present on Cronet or OkHttp.\r\n\r\nWhile OkHttp could be used as a network stack of ExoPlayer, I noticed when testing the usage of the OkHttp extension for playback that throttling issues with playback of YouTube contents may happen. That's the reason why Cronet is used instead, on which the issue does not happen, according to my tests since a few months.\r\n\r\nThe addition of this network library, embedded into the application, increases unfortunately the application size by around 10MB, because the Cronet library contains native code, shipped for all CPU architectures supported by Android's NDK (`arm64-v8a`, `armeabi-v7a`, `x86` and `x86_64`).\r\n\r\nThis **doubles the release application size**, due to the fact that the application is universal and not architecture dependant. I can enable split APKs support to allow creation of single architecture APKs (while also keeping an universal APK) in a separate pull request.\r\n\r\nThe QUIC protocol has a User-Agent ID property. On Cronet, it is composed of the name of the application using Cronet and ` Cronet/` + Cronet's version. This ID cannot be edited by third-party clients, unless they replace the code which sets this User-Agent ID, by using a custom `cronet-common` module, module on which Cronet's embedded variant depends.\r\n\r\nIn order to avoid services to fingerprint NewPipe with QUIC's User-Agent ID while being able to use QUIC protocol, a Gradle \"hack\" of the `cronet-common` module, which replaces the `UserAgent` class by our custom implementation, has been added, thanks to Stypox for that.\r\n\r\nAs `YoutubeHttpDataSource` was a copy of ExoPlayer's DefaultHttpDataSource, based on Android's network stack, which is now unused, it has been removed and the modifications made for YouTube playback on streaming URLs are now made using a [`ResolvingDataSource` `Resolver`](https://exoplayer.dev/doc/reference/com/google/android/exoplayer2/upstream/ResolvingDataSource.Resolver.html), `YoutubeDataSourceResolver`.\r\n    \r\nA workaround is used in it to prevent ExoPlayer sending the Range HTTP header. If usage of the range query parameter/path parameter is enabled and that it doesn't already exist as a URL parameter, this header is converted into a range query parameter or \"path parameter\".\r\n\r\nThis may break playback if YouTube is serving streaming data with compression, which is unlikely to happen as:\r\n- it is inefficient;\r\n- Cronet doesn't allow editing the `Accept-Encoding` HTTP header (see https://groups.google.com/a/chromium.org/g/net-dev/c/VbWPhyGrxD4/m/VC71PP3DAQAJ for details about how Cronet handles content encoding)\r\n- the YouTube official Android app uses it, according to reverse engineering that I made on a recent build of the app (the build was a 18 major one).\r\n\r\nThis resolver adds support of YouTube `videoplayback` URLs using \"path parameters\" instead of query parameters. For example, `https://YOUTUBE_VIDEO_HOST.com/videoplayback/PARAM_1/VALUE_1/PARAM_2/VALUE_2` is using \"path parameters\", when `https://YOUTUBE_VIDEO_HOST.com/videoplayback?PARAM_1=VALUE_1&PARAM_2=VALUE_2` query parameters. \"Path parameters\" are used for streaming URLs of DASH and HLS manifests.\r\n\r\nThis `Resolver` is compatible with multiple network stacks and is easier to maintain than the previous approach.\r\n\r\nTimeouts of network sockets connect and write operations have been increased, in the app except images, from the default values (10 seconds for each operation) to 30 seconds. It is now also the case for playback, while this value where has been set where it was possible (connect and read operations, their default value is 8 seconds in ExoPlayer).\r\n\r\n#### Known issues\r\nIf you switch from a network allowing QUIC connections to a one blocking the protocol, you may encounter network errors. There is nothing I can do to prevent this, except adding switches to disable QUIC on the app side.\r\n\r\n#### Fixes the following issue(s)\r\n- #5352 for playback\r\n\r\n#### APK testing\r\n\r\nThe APK can be found by going to the \"Checks\" tab below the title. On the left pane, click on \"CI\", scroll down to \"artifacts\" and click \"app\" to download the zip file which contains the debug APK of this PR.\r\n\r\n#### Due diligence\r\n\r\n- [x] I read the [contribution guidelines](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/blob/HEAD/.github/CONTRIBUTING.md).",
